            [
                <font color="#336699">06/Apr/26</font>

                            ]
            </font>

        </td></tr>
        <tr id="comment-body-264459"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p>Hi <a href="https://mikmakai.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0" class="user-hover" rel="712020:6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0" data-account-id="712020:6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0" accountid="712020:6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0" rel="noreferrer">seema.dhamija</a>, Could you please let me know which other two data drift algorithms I should implement?</p>
        </td></tr>
                <tr id="comment-header-264521"><td bgcolor="#f0f0f0">
            Comment by  
                                                    
                
        
            <a class="user-hover" rel="712020:6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0"
                id="word_commented_712020:6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0"
                href="https://mikmakai.atlassian.net/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?accountId=712020%3A6dd63376-8785-4213-9a08-216ba28731c0">
                    seema.dhamija
                </a>

                                        <font size="-2">
            [
                <font color="#336699">07/Apr/26</font>

                            ]
            </font>

        </td></tr>
        <tr id="comment-body-264521"><td bgcolor="#ffffff">
            <p>Hi Anish — I’ve reviewed the Notion document I shared earlier on the EDA-Driven Retraining Trigger Framework. For now, let’s prioritize <b>Scenario 2: Channel Activation/Deactivation</b> and <b>Scenario 3: Spend Mix Reallocation (structural, not volume)</b>.</p>

<p>Please let me know if you have any questions or need clarification on the code snippets I shared.</p>
        </td></tr>
